text:
Greenport Road, east side, north from Brookhaven to New Haven Aves., showing in the center of the view what Eugene L. Armbruster believes to be the former New York Hotel remodeled. (Note, do not confuse this hotel with Lelia's New York Hotel as both have the same title). It is now known as the Hotel Trouville. This is a set of two views. No. 2 shows the structure before it was remodeled.

May 1923.
View 2: About 1900.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
